Japan March large store sales up 14 . 1 pct yr / yr . Sales at Japanese department stores and supermarkets rose 14 . 1 percent in March from a year earlier to 2 . 27 trillion yen , the Ministry of International Trade and Industry ( MITI ) said on Monday . MITI attributed the increase mainly to purchases of clothing due to the change in seasons and " rush in " demand before the consumption tax increase from April 1 . For the fiscal year ended March 1997 , sales at Japanese department stores and supermarkets fell 0 . 4 percent from the previous year to 22 . 98 trillion yen , the ministry said . The breakdown for the figures is as follows : MAR FEB Overall change + 14 . 1 - 1 . 9 Dept stores + 21 . 1 - 0 . 1 Supermarkets + 7 . 2 - 3 . 4 
